## LSP Integration via Emacs

LSP is notoriously difficult to configure. Since it's already set up and working in Emacs, pi should leverage that rather than requiring separate LSP setup.

Useful LSP queries via Emacs:
- Go to definition (what file/line defines this symbol?)
- Find references (where is this used?)
- Get hover documentation
- List diagnostics (errors/warnings) for current buffer or project
- Get symbol information (type, signature, etc.)
- Code actions available at point

This avoids duplication of LSP infrastructure and ensures pi sees the same language intelligence that the user sees in their editor.
